    "infrastructure": {
      "rounds": [
        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`layer.path` from `architecture-rules.json` is joined to `root` and then scanned without any containment check. A malformed or malicious layer path like `../..` or an absolute path can make `verify doc-hidden` read files outside the trusted workspace.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "/home/flip451/individual/t-rust/templates/SoTOHE-core-003/libs/infrastructure/src/verify/doc_hidden.rs",
              "line": 50,
              "category": "trusted-root violation"
            },
            {
              "message": "`scan_rs_files` follows `read_dir` entries by calling `path.is_dir()` and `read_to_string()` without rejecting symlinks first. A symlinked `src/` subtree or file can redirect the scan outside the repo or create recursive traversal through symlink loops.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "/home/flip451/individual/t-rust/templates/SoTOHE-core-003/libs/infrastructure/src/verify/syn_helpers.rs",
              "line": 56,
              "category": "symlink not rejected at boundary"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:bdc5f37324f79cb0eef92f46ffc1185d4b14f2111e90caa16f8f489872393caa",
          "at": "2026-06-26T02:05:42Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "P1: [`doc_hidden.rs`](file:///home/flip451/individual/t-rust/templates/SoTOHE-core-003/libs/infrastructure/src/verify/doc_hidden.rs#L122) only checks top-level `syn::Item` variants and recurses into inline `mod` blocks. It does not descend into `impl`/`trait` bodies, struct fields, enum variants, or foreign items, so `#[doc(hidden)]` on public associated items or public fields/variants will be missed and the new gate can pass code that still produces the downstream `DanglingId` failure.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "/home/flip451/individual/t-rust/templates/SoTOHE-core-003/libs/infrastructure/src/verify/doc_hidden.rs",
              "line": 122,
              "category": "correctness"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:667b9bcb39253521d7a76219b805bbe609617d1a01e27ea6f70644bc016e665e",
          "at": "2026-06-26T02:18:04Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "zero_findings",
          "findings": [],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:aa3d2f7427d4db7856263374094b520fc74c35e052453a4a92ee6a481b5f2c0a",
          "at": "2026-06-26T02:27:38Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "A test-scoped inline module aborts scanning for the rest of the file. In the `syn::Item::Mod` arm, `return` exits `check_item`, so when `check_items` is iterating a file, any production items after `#[cfg(test)] mod tests` are never checked. That lets a later `#[doc(hidden)] pub ...` bypass this gate and still trigger the rustdoc/DanglingId failure the verifier is meant to prevent. Skip only that module instead of returning from the item scan.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "libs/infrastructure/src/verify/doc_hidden.rs",
              "line": 258,
              "category": "verifier-correctness"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:aa3d2f7427d4db7856263374094b520fc74c35e052453a4a92ee6a481b5f2c0a",
          "at": "2026-06-26T02:32:03Z"
        },
